   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.5244_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>15, Waterloo Place. S.W.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>September 19. <add place="above">th</add> 1878</dateline>



               <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I am sorry that I have not sooner been able to write to you about your novel <ref
                  target="#bib:Hardy1878_Native">"The Return of the Native"</ref>.</p>

            <p>I shall be happy to publish an edition of one thousand copies, and to pay you two
               hundred pounds (£200) on pub­lication, provided you can arrange for the appearance of
               the work in a separate form at least one month before it's com­pletion in the
               Magazine. In the event of there being a demand for further editions I would pay you
               £75 (seventy five pounds) for every 250 copies printed by us.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Believe me My dear Sir</salute>
               <salute>Yours very faithfully</salute>
               <signed>George Smith</signed>
               <note>Thomas Hardy <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></note>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.5244_2.jpg"/>

